# Aramiworks Core Standards

## Language & Style

- TypeScript strict mode; avoid `any`
- Conventional Commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, `perf:`, `refactor:`
- Korean comments OK for internal logic; English for public APIs/docs
- pnpm for package management

## Code Quality

- Functions < 50 lines; files < 300 lines
- Extract logic into named functions (no anonymous callback soup)
- Zod for all external input validation
- No `console.log` in production code — use structured logging

## Git & PRs

- Branch naming: `feature/xxx`, `fix/xxx`, `chore/xxx`, `docs/xxx`
- PR title = Conventional Commit format
- Link Linear issue in PR description when relevant
- No direct push to main/master

## Security

- No hardcoded secrets — use env vars or 1Password
- Validate all user/external inputs
- Principle of least privilege for API tokens

## AI Context

When using AI tools in this repo:
- Check `CLAUDE.md` for project context
- Check `.cursor/rules/` for coding standards
- Check `AGENTS.md` for agent behavior rules
